ProtoResult:
. "Given an equivalence relation $\sim$ on a set $X$, the 
   equivalence classes of $X$ form a partition of $X$. 
   Conversely, if ${\mathcal P} = \{ X_i\}$ is a partition of a
   set $X$, then there is an equivalence relation on $X$ with 
   equivalence classes $X_i$."
